Technology giant Microsoft says they are looking forward to the fourth industrial revolution and the predicted positive outcomes it have might for South Africa. Speaking to SABC Digital News on the sidelines of the ITU conference in Durban,  Microsoft KZN Provincial Executive Sandile Mahlaba, says the focus of the company is to assist where possible to ensure that people in rural communities,  such as the Eastern Cape have access to connectivity to ensure that they can make the most of the technology which is being offered by Microsoft. Watch interview below: 